Henry Richard BELL v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 5456. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Sept. 13, 1956. Raymond D. Buckles, Denver, Colo., for appellant. Donald E. Kelley, U. S. Atty., and John S. Pfeiffer, Asst. U. S. Atty., Denver,, Colo., for appellee.

Before BRATTON, Chief Judge, and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judge.

Dismissed for failure of appellant diligently to prosecute the same.
